Reproductive system diorchic, opposed, outstretched. Anterior testis to left of intestine, posterior testis to right of intestine. Anterior testis with relatively large oval sperm cells (5-8 μm wide by 12-15 μm long) without nuclei (
Fig. 2A
). Posterior testis with smaller, oval-shaped sperm cells (up to 8×5 μm) with lenticular nuclei situated peripherally (
Fig. 2B
). Spicules paired, equal, 0.5-0.6 abd long, with lightly cuticularised, swollen proximal portion, and heavily cuticularised, pointed distal portion. Gubernaculum not observed. Large rectal gland surrounds spicules. Four small, tubular pre-cloacal supplements, one pre-cloacal seta. Tail conico-cylindrical, with several short caudal setae and three short terminal setae. Three caudal glands and spinneret.
